            <p><strong><a href="http://www.sociallyawareblog.com/2016/12/06/new-copyright-office-rule-creates-potential-gotcha-for-blogs-and-websites-hosting-user-generated-content/" target="_blank">New Copyright Office Rule Creates Potential “Gotcha” for Blogs and Websites Hosting User-Generated Content</a></strong></p>
            <p>A recent change at the U.S. Copyright Office might expose blogs and websites to copyright infringement claims if they do not take certain preventive measures. The Copyright Office recently rolled out a new online system for the designation of agents to receive notifications of copyright infringement, which replaces the old paper-based system. Online service providers must register their copyright agent through the new system by December 31, 2017, in order to continue receiving the benefits of the Section 512(c) safe harbor in connection with its hosting of user-generated content.</p>
