            <p><strong><a href="http://abovethelaw.com/2016/12/lawsuit-against-courts-massively-overcharging-for-documents-moves-forward/" target="_blank">Lawsuit Against Courts for Allegedly Overcharging for Documents Via PACER Moves Forward</a></strong></p>
            <p>A federal judge ruled against the U.S. government in a case alleging that PACER, the federal court system’s electronic records system, charges unreasonable fees for the service it provides. The judge found unpersuasive the government’s arguments supporting its motion to dismiss for failure to state a claim, as well as its argument that the pricing issue was already being raised in another similar lawsuit.</p>
