            <p><strong><a href="http://www.abajournal.com/news/article/aba_sues_over_feds_disqualifications_of_lawyers_from_public_service_loan_fo" target="_blank">ABA Sues Over Feds’ Disqualification of Lawyers From Public Service Forgiveness Program</a></strong></p>
            <p>Current and former employees of the American Bar Association have filed a lawsuit against the U.S. Department of Education over changes to its Public Service Loan Forgiveness program, which helps lawyers working for certain service organizations repay their education loans. The ABA is one of several organizations that formerly qualified for the PSLF program but was recently denied certification. Other organizations include the American Immigration Lawyers Association and some American Civil Liberties Union offices.</p>
