            <p><strong><a href="http://www.abajournal.com/news/article/software_issues_lead_to_wrongful_arrests_pd_says_can_fruits_of_computerized" target="_blank">Courthouse Software Issues Have Led to Wrongful Arrests, Public Defender Says</a></strong></p>
            <p>A public defender in Alameda County, California, alleges that the Odyssey Case Manager software, which was recently adopted in that county, led to the wrongful arrests of dozens of people. Apparently the same software is used by 26 court systems throughout California, as well as other courts in other parts of the country. Known to be very cumbersome to use, the software has allegedly caused multiple wrongful arrests and unwarranted, additional jail time.</p>
